# Mountain Twig Games — Cursor Rules
# This file gives the AI full context about the project.
# Read this before making any edits.

## What this is
A multi-game mobile platform built by a solo developer.
Each game is a standalone Capacitor app (iOS + Android).
All games share one Supabase backend, one coin wallet, and one referral engine.
Cross-promotion between games is the core growth mechanic.

## Company
Mountain Twig Games
Domain: mountaintwìggames.com
Bundle ID prefix: games.mountaintwig

## Stack — never suggest alternatives to these
- Monorepo: Turborepo + pnpm workspaces
- Hub frontend: Next.js 14 (App Router) + Tailwind CSS
- Backend: Next.js API routes (no separate server)
- Database: Supabase Postgres + Drizzle ORM
- Auth: Supabase Auth (email + Google)
- Cache: Upstash Redis
- Games: Phaser 3 + TypeScript + Vite
- Mobile: Capacitor (one app per game)
- Deep links: Branch.io
- Analytics: Amplitude
- Deploy: Vercel (hub), Capacitor (games)
- Language: TypeScript everywhere, strict mode

## Monorepo structure
apps/hub          — Next.js platform hub (wallet, catalog, profile, referral)
apps/game-01      — First game (Phaser 3 + Capacitor)
apps/game-02      — Second game (same scaffold)
packages/sdk      — @mtwg/sdk — imported by every game
packages/types    — @mtwg/types — all shared TypeScript interfaces
packages/db       — @mtwg/db — Drizzle schema + client
packages/game-scaffold — template copied for each new game

## Critical rules — never break these

### 1. Idempotency key on every coin grant
Every call to /api/rewards/grant must include idempotency_key.
Format: `{reason}-{userId}-{contextId}`
Example: `level_complete-abc123-level-5`
The unique constraint on reward_ledger.idempotency_key prevents duplicates.

### 2. Ledger before balance — always
reward_ledger INSERT must happen before wallets UPDATE in the same transaction.
Never update wallet balance without a ledger entry.
Never UPDATE or DELETE reward_ledger rows — append only.

### 3. Two Redis clusters
session Redis — auth tokens, session state
ad Redis — frequency caps, campaign pacing
Never use session Redis in ad-related code and vice versa.

### 4. SDK auth is direct Supabase — not postMessage
Games authenticate directly via @supabase/supabase-js in the SDK.
There is no iframe. Each game is its own native Capacitor app.
Never suggest iframe or postMessage patterns.

### 5. Deep links via Branch.io only
Cross-promo attribution uses Branch.io deferred deep links.
apple-app-site-association lives at apps/hub/public/.well-known/
Never suggest custom deep link implementations.

### 6. App store compliance
Each game is a separate App Store submission.
Games must never load executable code from remote URLs at runtime.
Cross-promotion opens Branch.io deep links — not iframes or webviews loading other apps.

## Database schema (key tables)
users           — mirrors Supabase auth.users, one row per player
wallets         — one row per player, softBalance = current coins
reward_ledger   — append-only, every earn/spend, unique idempotency_key
games           — game catalog, slug matches SDK game ID
user_games      — tracks which games a player has installed (for ad filtering)
campaigns       — cross-promo campaigns, budgetCoins/spentCoins tracked
referrals       — referral codes, one per user, resolved on first install

## API routes (all in apps/hub/app/api/)
POST /api/auth/register          — ensure user + wallet exist (called by SDK init)
GET  /api/wallet                 — balance + recent ledger
POST /api/rewards/grant          — ledger-first coin grant, idempotent
POST /api/rewards/daily-login    — daily streak claim, Upstash Redis TTL
GET  /api/ads                    — best cross-promo campaign for this player/game
POST /api/events                 — track game event to Amplitude + platform
GET  /api/referral/my-code       — get/create referral code + share URL
POST /api/referral/resolve       — resolve referral, grant coins to both parties
POST /api/referral/resolve-crosspromo — resolve cross-promo install attribution

## SDK usage pattern (every game uses this)
import { createMTWG } from '@mtwg/sdk'
const mtwg = createMTWG('game-01')
const { userId, balance } = await mtwg.init()
await mtwg.grantCoins('level_complete', 50, `level_complete-${userId}-level-5`)
const ad = await mtwg.getAd()

## Coin earn rates
install_reward:    500 coins
first_session:     200 coins
level_complete:     50 coins
daily_login:       100 coins
streak_bonus day3: 300 coins
streak_bonus day7: 1000 coins
referral_install:  750 coins (referrer) + 250 coins (new player)

## Code style
- TypeScript strict mode always
- Zod for all API request validation
- No any types unless absolutely unavoidable with a comment explaining why
- Error handling: catch Postgres error code 23505 for idempotency duplicates
- All API routes return NextResponse.json()
- Use drizzle-orm query builder — no raw SQL except for sql template literals
- Tailwind for all hub styling — no CSS modules, no styled-components
- Dark theme: bg-neutral-950 base, bg-neutral-900 cards, text-neutral-100
- Brand orange: #FF6A00, brand purple: #6A1B9A

## Week by week build status
Week 1: Monorepo scaffold, DB schema, SDK skeleton, hub shell — IN PROGRESS
Week 2: Identity + wallet + coin grant
Week 3: SDK + Branch.io + Capacitor scaffold
Week 4-5: Game #1 build + mobile
Week 6: Cross-promo engine
Week 7: Referral engine
Week 8: Rewards UI + daily streak
Week 9: Game #2
Week 10: App Store submissions

